# OTM Cyber AI Development Agent Demo

## What this shows
An AI development agent working on re-platforming tasks while your human developers continue firefighting - proving two-track development is possible.

## Run it
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python main.py
```

Then open: http://localhost:8000

## What to say during the demo

### Opening (30 seconds)
"This is your development dashboard showing both tracks running simultaneously. On the left, your human devs are handling the usual fires - field nodes down, SOC alerts. On the right, our AI agent is making real progress on your new platform backlog."

### Key talking points
- **Two-track approach**: AI handles new development while humans firefight
- **Real code generation**: Agent writes actual implementation code, not just pseudocode
- **Security-first**: Every AI-generated change goes through SOC 2 compliance checking
- **Backlog integration**: Pulls directly from your Jira/Linear setup
- **Progress visibility**: See exactly what the AI accomplished while you were in meetings

### Production version differences
- Connects to your actual Jira/Linear instead of mock data
- Integrates with your real repositories and CI/CD pipeline  
- Uses your specific tech stack and coding standards
- Includes your custom security policies and compliance rules

## If something breaks
Click "Load Fallback Data" in the top right to show mock progress if live updates fail.

## What questions they'll ask

**"How do we know the AI won't break our production systems?"**
→ "The AI only works on the NEW platform code. Your current system stays untouched. Plus every change gets reviewed through your existing security and code review process."

**"What if the AI makes mistakes?"** 
→ "All AI-generated code goes through the same testing and review pipeline as human code. The difference is the AI can work nights and weekends while your team sleeps."

**"How long to get this running?"**
→ "2-3 weeks to train the agent on your specific requirements and integrate with your systems. Then it starts contributing immediately while we refine its output based on your feedback."
